cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with the optimization of wireless communication using UAVs as flying base stations and employs non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) for multiuser communication. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper deals with wireless communication, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the optimization of a system, cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a path-following algorithm, and cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper considers the throughput of wireless communication.
